OL,5, A vulnerable young woman is locked on  
OL,6, the other side of a thick glass window,
OL,7, crying like I have never heard anyone  
OL,8, cry before.                            
OL,10,FFor hours I have been sitting outside  
OL,11,Fthe small room, listening to her       
OL,12,Fdesperate pleas to be let out.         
OL,14,FThis is the image that haunts me from  
OL,15,Fthe three months I spent working       
OL,16,Fundercover for BBC Panorama as a       
OL,17,Fhealthcare support worker.             
OL,20,FIt could be a frightening place for    
OL,21,Fpatients and staff.                    
